      "lineNumber": 5,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "An explicit null is a real, typed, present value (Type \u0022null\u0022) occupying the variable \u2014 it is\nNOT the same as a never-set variable (which resolves to not-found). Here we pin the value side:\nassigning null yields a present null-typed value that reads back as null.",
